<item>
            <title>[BCEL-249] Check for max Short seems wrong</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BCEL-249</link>
                <project id="12314220" key="BCEL">Commons BCEL</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are some checks for the max  value that will fit in a short.&lt;br/&gt;
These are of the form:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.abs(value) &amp;gt;= 32767)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems wrong, as Short.MAX_VALUE = 32767, so the check should be&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.abs(value) &amp;gt; 32767)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a further problem, which is that Short.MIN_VALUE = -32768.&lt;br/&gt;
This will be disallowed, unless the condition is written as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((value &amp;gt;= -32768) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (value &amp;lt;= 32767))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is how the ctor generic.PUSH.PUSH(ConstantPoolGen cp, int value) does the check.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
